The '''''Ravens Bluff Trumpeter''''', or simply '''The Trumpeter''', was a monthly periodical [[broadsheet]] that reported on a wide variety of topics, from election coverage and war updates to preposterous scandals and opinion pieces, and even classifieds.{{Cite organized play/LC/A Boy and His Mammoth|20}}

{{quote|''Please do not talk about this matter with anyone. I really do not want my personal life to become a spectacle for those bloodthirsty leeches that work for the Trumpeter. I value my privacy.''|[[Glandryl Moonbow]]{{Cite organized play/LC/Everything Dies|5}}}}

Staff.Editorial:
*[[Fred Faber]], the Editor-in-Chief in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LC/Annie Would I Lie to You|27}}
*[[Strunk Norbert]], the Editor-in-Chief predecessor of master Faber.{{Cite polyhedron/97/The Ravens Bluff Trumpeter|32}}
*[[Cuthbert Ironbeard III]], an editorial contributor during Strunk Norbert's, the Editor-in-Chief's run.
*[[Clio Hesperin]], the reporter who run the ''City News'' column in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Damien Blackthorn]], a ninth shift editor in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Guido]], a poorly-educated dockside reporter in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Harold Dayspring]], one of the co-owners of the ''Ravens Bluff Trumpeter'', killed by a runaway chariot ''circa'' [[1372 DR]].{{Cite polyhedron/148/Pillars of Ravens Bluff|16}}
*[[Jacinth Moonspring]], the editor and reporter who handled the ''Society'' section of the broadsheet in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Whitney Wordsmlth]], the managing editor, who worked alongside Strunk Norbert, the Editor-in-Chief.
*[[Silva Sinaran]], a highborn society reporter from the late 14{{th}} century DR.

Staff.Reporters and Contributors:
*[[Al Kadeem]], an occasional contributor who covered topics associated with the [[Temple of Tyr (Ravens Bluff)|Temple of Tyr]] in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite trumpeter/1-6|2}}
*[[Alisuies Relthana]], a Lady [[Knight of the Mystic Flame]] and an occasional contributor who covered the unification of the [[Ministry of Art]] and the [[Wizard's Guild]] in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Amber Lynn Thoden]], ironically enough, the alter-ego of the infamous warlord and enemy of Ravens Bluff and one of the regular contributors.{{Cite trumpeter/1-2|2}}
*[[Armond Arhesian]], the reporter who penned articles on Ambassador [[Belakira]] of [[Thay]] in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite trumpeter/1-9|3}}
*[[Borrek Halloway]], a journalist who was murdered in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LC/Night Shift|2-3}}
*[[Dilyard Noonbar]], a journalist who penned ''New Threat to City Says Wizard's Guild'' in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite trumpeter/1-4|2}}
*[[Gandalf Wishspoon]], a journalist killed in a gang war of [[Crow's End]] in [[1370 DR]].{{Cite polyhedron/119/The Ravens Bluff Trumpeter|31}}
*[[Harold Dayspring]], one of the ''Tumpeter's'' reporters who penned articles on breaking news, such as ''Brazen Attack Against Lord Blacktree'' in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LC/Elementally Speaking: Air's Looking at You|25}}
*[[Jonah Mindspring]], the reporter who held an interview with the Senior [[Harper]] in Ravens Bluff in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite trumpeter/2-10|1}}
*[[Nadd Parker]], a freelance reporter in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite trumpeter/1-8|1}}
*[[Rupert T. Hangman]], a judge who penned conviction announcements for ''The Trumpeter'' in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Silva Sinaran]], a manorborn society reporter and Lord [[Imbrel]]'s youngest sister in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LC/A Simple Pick Up|5}}
*[[Symore Ceasmore]], a reporter who covered major announcements from the Ministry of Art in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite trumpeter/1-5|2-3}}
*[[Tara Strongquill]], a dockside reporter who was abducted by the city's criminal elements in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LC/News of the World|3-4}}
*[[Terrance Heldersporn]], a reporter who penned articles about the [[Temple of Selûne (Ravens Bluff)|Temple of Selûne]] in Ravens Bluff.
*[[Toby Wartwarden]], a journalist who penned the ''Bandits of the Red Sun Raid Ravens Bluff Caravans'' article in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LC/Silk and Assassins|22}}
*[[Tomaldi Everspring]], a late 14{{th}} century DR employee of the ''Trumpeter'' and a contributor who wrote about religious organizations.{{Cite trumpeter/1-1|2}}
*[[Victoria Morales]], a sea captain and an occasional contributor in the late 14{{th}} century DR.

document_data.History:
In [[Ches]] of the {{YearlinkName|1368}}, a ''Trumpeter'' clerk – [[Myra Miller]], received a mention in that month's issue of ''Ravens Bluff Trumpeter''. After the offices of the gazette were ransacked and torched (evidently by [[Talassan]]s) while the staff was away at the local printer's shop, Myra showed quick thinking and managed to save the organization's documents from being destroyed. Despite Myra Miller's best efforts, all reports of the summer meteor crisis of the {{YearlinkName|1367}} were lost.

In the {{YearlinkName|1369}}, one of the casualties in the recent gang war was [[Borrek Halloway]], a journalist who worked for ''The Trumpeter's'' ninth shift editor [[Damien Blackthorn]]. Borrek was just the latest among a series of grizzly killings, and a group of the Living City adventurers answered a summoning from the editor and accepted his contract to uncover the truth behind the victim's death. Borrek's killing could've been the result of his work on such investigative pieces as ''Corruption in the City Government'', ''Bribery in the City Watch'', ''Merchant's Guild Inflating Prices'', and ''Organized Criminal Guilds: Parasites of Society''.

In the {{YearlinkName|1375}}, ''The Trumpeter's'' best investigative reporter, Tara Strongquill, fell victim to a kidnapping by the notorious chaos agent named [[Locaath Blackmanta]]. The kidnapping was a stunt aimed to sew panic in Ravens Bluff. The ''Ravens Bluff Trumpeter'' hired a band of adventurers to find the culprit and rescue the unlucky supporter.{{Cite organized play/LC/News of the World|31}}
